record_data.record_plain_text: RAUSCH CREEK GENERATION, LLC Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Rausch Creek Generation, LLC ("RCG") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Power Service") from its RCG Generating Station facility located in Joliett, Pennsylvania to the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Reactive Service Tariff sets forth RCG's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Power Service to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides for PJM to pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirements for Reactive Power Service. RCG's monthly revenue requirement was established pursuant to a Commission Order approving a Settlement Agreement filed on April 30, 2018 in Docket Nos. EL18-57-000 and ER18-15-000, et al. This revenue requirement replaces the revenue requirement previously submitted for filing by RCG and shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. RCG's annual revenue requirement is $72,765.00. MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: RCG's total monthly revenue requirement is $6,063.75 ($72,765.00/12 = $6,063.75).
